<p><i><b>Beneath a Steel Sky</b></i> is a <a href="/wiki/United_Kingdom" title="United Kingdom">British</a> <a href="/wiki/1994_in_video_gaming" title="1994 in video gaming">1994</a> <a href="/wiki/Science_fiction" title="Science fiction">science fiction</a> <a href="/wiki/Point_and_click" title="Point and click" class="mw-redirect">point and click</a> <a href="/wiki/Adventure_game" title="Adventure game">adventure game</a> in the <a href="/wiki/Cyberpunk" title="Cyberpunk">cyberpunk</a> genre. It featured comedy elements and was <a href="/wiki/Video_game_developer" title="Video game developer">developed</a> by <a href="/wiki/Revolution_Software" title="Revolution Software">Revolution Software</a> and <a href="/wiki/Video_game_publisher" title="Video game publisher">published</a> by <a href="/wiki/Virgin_Interactive_Entertainment" title="Virgin Interactive Entertainment" class="mw-redirect">Virgin Interactive Entertainment</a>. It was initially released for <a href="/wiki/DOS" title="DOS">DOS</a> and <a href="/wiki/Amiga" title="Amiga">Amiga</a>. <i>Underworld</i> was its working title.</p>
<table id="toc" class="toc" summary="Contents">
